This data set includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area.

  • Trip Duration (seconds)
  • Start Time and Date

total = df.shape[0]

total_M = df.member_gender[df.member_gender == 'Male'].count()
total_F = df.member_gender[df.member_gender == 'Female'].count()
total_O = df.member_gender[df.member_gender == 'Other'].count()

M_subscribers = df.member_gender[(df.member_gender == 'Male')&(df.user_type == 'Subscriber')].count()
F_subscribers = df.member_gender[(df.member_gender == 'Female')&(df.user_type == 'Subscriber')].count()
O_subscribers = df.member_gender[(df.member_gender == 'Other')&(df.user_type == 'Subscriber')].count()

M_customers = df.member_gender[(df.member_gender == 'Male')&~(df.user_type == 'Subscriber')].count()
F_customers = df.member_gender[(df.member_gender == 'Female')&~(df.user_type == 'Subscriber')].count()
O_customers = df.member_gender[(df.member_gender == 'Other')&~(df.user_type == 'Subscriber')].count()

M_subscribers_prop = M_subscribers / total_M
F_subscribers_prop = F_subscribers  / total_F
O_subscribers_prop = O_subscribers / total_O

M_customers_prop = M_customers / total_M
F_customers_prop = F_customers / total_F
O_customers_prop = O_customers / total_O

print(M_subscribers_prop)
print(F_subscribers_prop)

print(M_customers_prop)
print(F_customers_prop)
